# Employee Lifecycle Tab — Integration Checklist

Any time you add or change an onboarding/offboarding step, ask: **does this action have a matching `lifecycle_checklist_definitions` item, and should it auto-complete it?**

## How auto-sync works

`backend/src/services/lifecycleSync.service.js` → `syncLifecycleItems(userId)` is called on every Lifecycle tab load. It reads existing app data and calls `UserLifecycleChecklistItem.autoComplete()` for each non-manual item.

Current `integration_type` resolvers:

| type | what it reads |
|------|--------------|
| `document_task` | `tasks` where `task_type='document'` and `status='completed'`; title matched by `integration_ref` substring |
| `training_task` | `tasks` where `task_type='training'` and `status='completed'`; track name matched |
| `user_info_field` | `user_info_values` for the `integration_ref` field key — non-empty = complete |
| `account_setup` | `users.email` populated (workspace provisioned) |
| `credentialing` | `user_insurance_credentialing.status = 'approved'` |
| `supervision_session` | finalized `supervision_sessions` row exists for supervisee |

## When to act

### Adding a new document template to onboarding/pre-hire packages
→ Check if there is a matching `item_key` in `lifecycle_checklist_definitions` with `integration_type = 'document_task'`.
→ If yes, make sure `integration_ref` substring matches the template title/type.
→ If no matching item, consider adding one to migration 880 or a follow-up migration.

### Adding a new training focus/module to onboarding packages
→ Same pattern — check `training_task` definitions. `integration_ref` should match the track name/slug.

### Adding a new onboarding status transition (e.g. a new status between ONBOARDING → ACTIVE_EMPLOYEE)
→ Add `syncLifecycleItems(userId)` call in `user.controller.js` at that transition point.
→ Status-based lifecycle items use `integration_type = 'status'` (currently manual only — hook pending Phase 2).

### Adding a new user_info field that confirms HR completion (e.g. "cleared_to_start")
→ Add a `lifecycle_checklist_definitions` row with `integration_type = 'user_info_field'` and `integration_ref = 'your_field_key'`.
→ No code change needed — the resolver picks it up automatically.

### Adding new offboarding steps or access-removal automation
→ Add checklist definitions to `lifecycle_checklist_definitions` under the appropriate `category` (`access_removal`, `property_return`, `final_employment`).
→ If the step can be auto-detected (e.g. workspace disabled via API), add a resolver case in `lifecycleSync.service.js`.

## Phase 2 hook points (future — add these as you build)

Call `syncLifecycleItems(userId)` (import from `lifecycleSync.service.js`) at:
- Document task completion (`tasks` update handler)
- Training focus step completion (`trainingFocusProgress.service.js`)
- User info value save (`userInfoValue.controller.js`)
- Credentialing approval (`agencyCredentialing.controller.js`)
- `mark-complete`, `mark-terminated`, `promote-to-onboarding` in `user.controller.js`

